What is PublicSquare?

The new path to homeownership


Move into any home for just 2.5%, then buy it off us later for a guaranteed purchase price. It's rent-to-own homes by PublicSquare.

PublicSquare is a first-mover fintech company in the rent-to-buy real estate space. The company makes homeowning accessible to one million creditworthy households in Australia who still don’t own their own home due to high deposit requirements.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Growth Strategy

  • Continue driving demand through $0 CAC, high-quality customer acquisition
  • Acquire highly secure, low-risk properties focused on modern homes in good-quality suburbs
  • Operate a lean, long-term focused business model that reinvests free cash flow into additional property acquisitions to compound growth
  • Onboard sophisticated strategic partnerships (e.g. institutional investors, and developers) to ensure profitable returns for shareholders
  • Continually optimise the cost of capital with a preference for fixed rates or semi-fixed funding stacks during the growth stage, then pivot to off-balance sheet funding solutions at scale (e.g. warehouse funding)
  • Offset most transactional and maintenance costs through customer contributions

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Problem and Market

Home loan products no longer match the financial circumstances of the average homebuyer. It now takes Australian homebuyers an average of 10+ years to save a deposit.

Why does it take so long to save a deposit? Because the median house-price-to-income-ratio in Australia has gone from around 3x in the 1970s to around 10x now. So, if you live in a city, make an average salary, and don’t have help from mum (or don’t want to live them while you save), owning your own home has become a pipedream.

In the U.S, where home prices are lower than in Australia, rent-to-buy home providers such as Divvy and Landis, have successfully placed tens of thousands of customers into homes over the past four years.

Therefore the market cap for the rent-to-buy homes sector is currently in the range of $20-$30 billion, growing year over year and shared amongst just a handful of competitors.

In Australia, the sector is just getting started. Alternative home-buying solutions such as PublicSquare are early and inevitable, and the success of one or more competitors, including PublicSquare, is imminent.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The PublicSquare Solution

PublicSquare provides a beautiful software and customer service experience offering life-changing financial upside to qualified homebuyers.

The company's rent-to-buy product works like this:

  • You pay a 2.5% kickstarter payment;
  • You move in as a renter while you build up your equity towards a purchase (typically 2-3% per year);
  • You buy the home when you're ready for a guaranteed, fixed purchase price.

Full product information can be found at the company’s website: www.publicsquare.com.au

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Competitive Advantage

PublicSquare has developed a substantial first mover advantage by securing an extensive lead in the online search space (namely organic SEO rankings on Google) for dozens of high incentive rent-to-buy and rent-to-own home-related keywords. This positioning currently produces over 500 organic customer signups per month, which are growing month over a month alongside recognition for the rent-to-buy category.

There is currently only one direct competitor to PublicSquare in Australia who is also early stage. Any new entrants to the space will experience significant legal and tax discovery hurdles and high initial capital requirements. The recent cooling in the capital markets will also lessen the possibility of new competition.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Use of Funds & Exit Strategy

Funds will be used to place up to 20 additional customers in homes within the next 6 months and surpass over $1m of gross annual recurring revenue. PublicSquare will also carry out strategic business and product development for attracting investment from institutional and managed funds while also locking in a subsequent round of venture capital within the next 12 months.

Recent M&A Activity in the US, including Blackrock’s $6BN acquisition of Home Partners of America, demonstrates strong corporate interest in acquiring high cashflow startups such as PublicSquare.

Moreover, PublicSquare’s Founder has the proven ability and resilience required to deliver consistent growth leading to a profitable exit for the company’s shareholders.

Fees

Investors invest through a VentureCrowd Trust, which is managed as a single asset by VentureCrowd. We don’t charge any annual management fee to investors, rather we only charge a performance fee where an exit delivers profit, thereby aligning ourselves with the outcomes for investors.

  • Contribution Fee: 1.1% This is the fee charged by the Trustee for the establishment of the Trust and the purchasing entity, structuring the overall investment and raising capital by way of issue of Units. Payable upon acceptance of your investment by the Trustee.
  • Management Fee: 1.65% per annum (charged upon conversion or exit).
  • Performance Fee: 20% of the profit (charged upon conversion or exit).
